	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I recently ran into this guy.<BR>
<BR>
With a team of some guild mates we were going to hunt HG's here in Rathe Mountains. We were with 4 of us, a lvl 39 wizzie, 36 mage, 38 druid and me as being a lvl 42 warrior then. <BR>
<BR>
When we arrived the old group just managed to charge out because they were all under lvl 35 and didn't manage Broog at all. <BR>
<BR>
I did never see this drunken fella so I decided to con him. He was red to me and while I done it, he was on his way to beat me up. <BR>
<BR>
I ran back to my 3 friends. I told them we got a BIG bait here. We were all laughing to him because we were kinda sure we wouldn't make a chance on him, while he was hitting me for a fair 100+ double/triple easy. <BR>
<BR>
I taunted a couple times, druid snared Broog and healed me up. Here the fight started. Our wizard started casting his mid/powerfull spells at the being, I taunted some more and the mage joined in casting now too. While Broog was chasing me and I ran a bit each time, catching a couple blows of him some times, the other 3 were nuking and healing. The wizzie was nuking like hell and so was the mage. <BR>
<BR>
After a couple minutes of straight nuking/running/taunting etc etc everyone was OOM and I was low on hps. We had Broog down to 2/3 of his hps :-(<BR>
<BR>
As you see he has a crap load of hps, we figured around 7-8k.<BR>
<BR>
While we ran out of the Hg's valley Broog was still chasing me. The 3 went up the walls medding like crazy getting up to 80%. In meanwhile I showed Broog half of the zone and he showed me what a read headache is about ;-)<BR>
<BR>
The other 3 announced that they were on some mana again, and I pulled Broog back into our 'Arena'. This time both the casters were going for full nukes which came trough fully. After a few nukes each time he went off to chase them and I was able to do some neat melee damage in those times while I was taunting him off. <BR>
<BR>
In the battle itself we had some real close calls. Our druid managed to get out of his blows two times with no more then 20 hps left. For myself I was dependant on the druid who had to heal me now and then since Broog hits HARD. Even with a fair bunch of warrior hps you'll see your bubs going down as a rain. <BR>
<BR>
Again the wizzie and the mage went oom. Broog was now in a 1/4 of hps. Everyone in the zone who had run away from him before ran into him promptly which ended out to a massive melee train on him. While the wizzie and the mage were medding a bit the druid started casting some rather neat nukes on him so he would face the druid. While he was doing that the melee train was doing 100's of damage easy. <BR>
<BR>
In a few minutes the wizzie stand up again and gave him the final nuke. The whole zone cheered and everyone was glad this drunken fella was taken down. <BR>
<BR>
Whatever comment you may have on this fight, it was an awesome deal to kill this guy with the team of us 4. If we wouldn't try, the beast would have tried to kill many others. So I think it was good we managed out -)<BR>
<BR>
At the end of battle two another HG ran into us which end up in me having 13 hps when I reached safe terrain and the rest of the zone turning these friends down. <BR>
<BR>
okay okay I was chickening then on the last two HG's but I'm proud to have had the chance to tank Broog.<BR>
<BR>
hehehehe<BR>
<BR>
Greetings<BR>
Hador ~Circle of Chatzuk~<BR>
Cazic-Thule server 
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
